"'''Tongue-tied: Bubo's Tale'''" by [[Daryl F. Mallett]] appeared in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' which was published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]] and is about [[Buboicullaar/Legends|Bubo]] the [[Frog-dog/Legends|frog-dog]], who ended up as a [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr Monk]].

==Plot summary==
[[Buboicullaar/Legends|Buboicullaar]] is yet another of the dregs within [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's palace]] plotting the [[Gangster/Legends|gangster's]] demise. Bubo thinks he has an advantage over his adversaries in that many assume him to be an unintelligent creature – but his disadvantage is that he is in fact not very bright. After [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] [[Death/Legends|death]], the [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr monks]] [[Brain/Legends|disembrain]] Bubo. Soon after his enlightenment, Buboicullaar recounts the story of how he got his revenge on [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]] to his long time mentor, [[Evilo Nailati]].

